This function works by repeatedly dividing the search interval in half. If the value of the search key is less than the item in the middle of the interval, the function continues to search the lower half. Otherwise, it continues to search the upper half. Repeatedly dividing the search interval in half requires log2n steps, making search algorithms like binary search much faster than others.
